(5672, 'nitroglycerin lingual', 'N/A', 'contraindicated', 'DRUG INTERACTIONS 7.1 PDE-5-Inhibitors and sGC-Stimulators Nitroglycerin Lingual Spray is contraindicated in patients who are using a selective inhibitor of cyclic guanosine monophosphate (cGMP)-specific phosphodiesterase type 5 (PDE-5). Nitroglycerin Lingual Spray is contraindicated in patients who are taking soluble guanylate cyclase (sGC) stimulators. Beta-adrenergic blockers blunt the reflex tachycardia produced by nitroglycerin without preventing its hypotensive effects.', 'DailyMed'),
